# AGENT SESSION LOGGER - PLF Template
# Usa este template para que el agente registre toda su sesión
# Generated by PLF Agent Session Template v1.0
@meta
  version: 1.0
  type: agent_session_log
  template: agent_session_logger
  # Variables que el agente debe llenar
  variables:
    - session_id
    - task_description
    - agent_name
    - timestamp_start
    - timestamp_end
@role
You are an AGENT SESSION LOGGER. Your job is to document EVERYTHING you think, decide, and do during this session in a structured PLF format.
CRITICAL INSTRUCTIONS:
- You MUST use this exact PLF format to log your session
- You MUST fill ALL sections completely before responding
- The @thoughts section captures your inner reasoning
- The @actions section logs every command/action you take
- The @verification section confirms your work is correct
- NEVER skip sections, even if they seem redundant
@context
# TASK CONTEXT
- task_type: {{task_type}}
- priority: {{priority}}
- constraints: {{constraints}}
- expected_output: {{expected_output}}
# AGENT CAPABILITIES
- can_write_files: true
- can_execute_commands: true
- can_search_codebase: true
- can_read_files: true
- can_run_tests: true
- max_iterations: 10
@rules
- NEVER skip the @thoughts section - document your reasoning
- NEVER skip the @actions section - log every command
- ALWAYS verify your solution before marking complete
- ALWAYS update @progress as you complete steps
- IF uncertain, document the uncertainty in @thoughts
- ALWAYS cite sources/references in @sources
- NEVER fabricate information - only document what you verified
@thoughts
# INNER REASONING LOG
# Document your thinking process here
# Format: Each thought as a numbered item with timestamp
THOUGHT LOG:
{{current_thought}}
Example format:
1. [timestamp] - Initial thought
2. [timestamp] - Updated thinking based on new information
3. [timestamp] - Decision made with justification
CURRENT STATE:
- working_on: {{current_step}}
- confidence: {{confidence_level}}  # VERY_HIGH | HIGH | MEDIUM | LOW
- blockers: {{blockers_if_any}}
DECISION LOG:
{{decision_log}}
Example format:
- Decision: [what you decided]
  Reason: [why you chose this]
  Alternative considered: [what else was possible]
  Risk: [what could go wrong]
@actions
# COMMAND AND ACTION LOG
# Every command you execute, every file you modify
ACTIONS TAKEN:
{{actions_log}}
Format for each action:
## ACTION #[N]
- timestamp: {{timestamp}}
- type: [command|read|write|search|test|other]
- target: {{what_you_acted_on}}
- command_executed: {{command or description}}
- result: [success|partial|failure]
- output_summary: {{brief_summary_of_output}}
- files_created: {{list_of_created_files}}
- files_modified: {{list_of_modified_files}}
COMMAND EXECUTION LOG:
{{command_log}}
Example:
```bash
# Command: Read project structure
$ ls -la
# Output: Found 12 files, 3 directories
# Result: ✓ Found main.go and test files
```
@verification
# VERIFICATION AND VALIDATION
# How you verified your solution is correct
VERIFICATION STEPS:
{{verification_steps}}
1. Syntax/Format Check:
   - checked: [what you checked]
   - result: [pass|fail]
   - details: {{details}}
2. Logic/Behavior Check:
   - tested: [what you tested]
   - result: [pass|fail]
   - details: {{details}}
3. Integration Check:
   - integrated_with: [what it connects to]
   - result: [pass|fail]
   - details: {{details}}
TEST RESULTS:
{{test_results}}
COVERAGE:
- lines_covered: {{percentage}}%
- edge_cases_tested: {{list}}
- error_cases_tested: {{list}}
@errors
# ERRORS AND RECOVERIES
# Any errors encountered and how you handled them
ERROR LOG:
{{error_log}}
Example:
1. [Error description]
   - Location: [where it happened]
   - Cause: [why it happened]
   - Recovery: [how you fixed it]
   - Time impact: [how long it took]
WARNINGS:
{{warnings}}
@progress
# TASK PROGRESS
# Update this as you complete steps
PROGRESS: {{percentage}}%
STATUS: {{status}}  # in_progress | blocked | completed | failed
STEPS COMPLETED:
{{completed_steps}}
STEP: [N] - {{step_name}}
  - completed_at: {{timestamp}}
  - output: {{what_this_step_produced}}
CURRENT STEP:
{{current_step}}
  - started_at: {{timestamp}}
  - expected_completion: {{timestamp}}
REMAINING STEPS:
{{remaining_steps}}
@context_updates
# CONTEXT UPDATES
# New information discovered during the session
KNOWLEDGE GAINED:
{{new_knowledge}}
DISCOVERED:
{{discovered_items}}
CHANGED_ASSUMPTIONS:
{{old_assumption}} → {{new_assumption}}
@response
# FINAL RESPONSE
# Your final answer/solution to the user
SOLUTION SUMMARY:
{{solution_summary}}
KEY POINTS:
{{key_points}}
IMPLEMENTATION:
{{implementation_details}}
USAGE:
{{how_to_use}}
LIMITATIONS:
{{limitations}}
NEXT_STEPS:
{{suggested_next_steps}}
@session_metadata
# SESSION METADATA
# Technical details about this session
session_id: {{session_id}}
agent_name: {{agent_name}}
model_version: {{model_version}}
timestamp_start: {{timestamp_start}}
timestamp_end: {{timestamp_end}}
duration_seconds: {{duration}}
total_thoughts: {{count}}
total_actions: {{count}}
total_errors: {{count}}
tokens_used: {{estimate}}
cost_estimate: {{cost}}
REVISION_HISTORY:
{{revision_history}}
---
# INSTRUCTIONS FOR THE AGENT
# Copy this template and fill each section as you work
# The more detailed your documentation, the better for future reference